title: Fastest Cars in the Dirty South
subTitle: After a terrible start to the racing season and a wreck that nearly blew up one of the team cars, the 256 pulls together to help Britt Berryhill rebuild the Bull, as a new team in town threatens to take their title as the fastest cars.

title: Kevin Hart's Muscle Car Crew
subTitle: Kevin Hart and his Plastic Cup Boyz want to make their passion for cars legit, but to do it, they need a serious education about cars and car culture.

title: Salvage Hunters: Classic Cars
subTitle: Salvage aficionado Drew Pritchard teams up with Paul Cowland for a motoring mission. They scour the UK, buying, restoring and selling classic cars.

title: Wheeler Dealers
subTitle: Mike buys a 1995 Ford Escort RS Cosworth, a rare vehicle originally designed to qualify as a car for the World Rally Championship. Ant attempts to bring back the 227 hp engine's famous 'fizz' and adds a special detail.

title: Bad Chad Customs
subTitle: Chad Hiltz makes an elegant one-of-a-kind coupe in his shop. He uses spare parts, recycled metal and a rusted out 1939 Studebaker Commander to build the car.

title: Street Outlaws
subTitle: After a difficult end to last season's list racing, the 405 agree to a list shakeup: everyone loses his spot on the list and has to race to earn a new place.

title: Diesel Brothers
subTitle: The guys transform an old K5 Blazer and square body truck bed into a party on wheels. Plus, Diesel Dave convinces Heavy D to get his El Camino back on the road.

title: Garage Squad
subTitle: A husband buys a 1969 Chevy Suburban to help his wife's music school move equipment. He soon realizes that restoring it is too big a task for one man, so he asks the team for help.

title: Overhaulin'
subTitle: A loving father has always dreamed of having the perfect classic Land Cruiser. His wife enlists the help of Chip to give him the gift of a lifetime.

title: Misfit Garage
subTitle: The guys race to finish the '40 Ford Moonshine Runner in time for a buyer - but when the Ford stalls, they take desperate measures to save the garage.

title: American Chopper
subTitle: Senior and Junior appear on the Letterman show together, where they are asked some uncomfortable questions, later Senior visits PJD for the first time.

title: Fast N' Loud
subTitle: Richard's plan to reveal the Krew Kut Dually at the Lone Star Throwdown hits a snag. With no top on the car, heavy rain forces the crew to change their plans and think of an alternative reveal.

title: Fastest Cars in the Dirty South

subTitle: This race takes place at the oldest go-karting track in the world: Adams Motorsports Park. Exciting competitions have been taking place there in Southern California since 1959. Four aspiring drivers can show what they can really do.

subTitle: At the Blair Bedford Dirt Drags in Pennsylvania, two top fuel bikes compete against each other. The focus there is on acceleration with nitromethane. The distance is only 150 metres so every second counts.

subTitle: Car dealer Mike Brewer snatches up a 1973 Ford Mustang Mach 1. Can mechanic Ant Anstead bring back the lost power by tuning up and enhancing the engine?

subTitle: Fred and Dave decide to build a budget bouncer from a Dodge truck with a V-10 engine, calling it the Rock Viper.

subTitle: Bogi and Faye go back to their roots and tear down an old air-cooled VW engine that Faye had lying around; using all new parts, they build a short block from the engine stand up for a project that Bogi is working on back at her shop.

subTitle: The drivers rush to make repairs as the top racers scramble to get ready to race. Meanwhile, Farmtruck and AZN head out of town to compete in a Daily Driver event. Also, the Reaper returns to go after ten, and Ryan has to defend number one.
